#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
lmstudio - interactive agent shell backed by LM Studio's OpenAI-compatible
local server. Mirrors Loom's in-app AgentOrchestrator (read/write/edit/
list/bash/update_tasks) and adds:

  - Slash commands  (/clear, /model, /bash, /cwd, /cost, /save, /resume,
                     /system, /sh, /tasks, /yolo, /theme, /help)
  - @file mentions with tab completion
  - Permission prompts (y/n/a) for write_file, edit_file, run_bash
  - Status footer above the boxed input
  - Auto-loaded project context (CLAUDE.md / AGENTS.md / GUIDE.md / README.md)
  - Inline unified diff for write_file / edit_file
  - Persistent session save / resume
  - Themes (default, mono, cyberpunk, solarized)
  - Ctrl-R reverse history search
  - JSON event stream output for scripting (--json)
  - Subagent dispatch tool (spawn_agent)
  - MCP server tool discovery (--mcp <stdio command>)

Stdlib only. Tasks are mirrored to ~/.loom/tasks/<session>/<id>.json so
Loom's Tasks pane picks them up.
"""

